WEBVTT

00:01.732 --> 00:04.299
Jeremy and I have
really started talking about

00:04.334 --> 00:06.438
leaving the business and getting out.

00:06.438 --> 00:07.369
Really?

00:07.404 --> 00:08.670
Don't go running off with Jeremy

00:08.705 --> 00:10.524
because he's the only person who asked.

00:10.524 --> 00:11.706
Run away with me.

00:11.741 --> 00:13.475
I know, Rach, about Adam.

00:13.510 --> 00:15.109
How many times are you gonna
make me look like a fool

00:15.145 --> 00:16.645
in front of these people?

00:16.680 --> 00:17.912
- Oh, my God.
- Don't do it.

00:17.947 --> 00:19.681
That's, uh... That's Hot Rachel.

00:19.716 --> 00:21.649
- So, this is the party truck, huh?
- You found it.

00:21.684 --> 00:23.384
Why don't you give me a tour?

00:23.419 --> 00:25.586
This season, our
suitor is more well-known.

00:25.621 --> 00:28.422
Ladies, are you ready? Darius Beck!

00:28.457 --> 00:30.991
Oh, my God. You like him.

00:31.026 --> 00:33.260
I went on a paleolithic
lifestyle retreat.

00:33.296 --> 00:35.492
And, uh, this show is my kingdom.

00:35.492 --> 00:37.030
"Everlasting" was my idea.

00:37.066 --> 00:38.065
Who's in charge here?

00:38.100 --> 00:39.432
- I am.
- I am.

00:39.467 --> 00:41.267
My two bosses are at
each other's throats.

00:41.303 --> 00:42.602
Coleman Wasserman.

00:42.637 --> 00:44.337
He is the one in charge now.

00:44.372 --> 00:47.607
You gave me the showrunner job
and essentially took it away.

00:47.642 --> 00:49.242
So you stabbed me in the back.

00:49.277 --> 00:50.743
Between you and me, we can make shows

00:50.778 --> 00:51.911
that actually mean something.

00:52.947 --> 00:54.214
You're the love of my life.

00:54.249 --> 00:56.047
I have a baby now. I'm responsible now.

00:56.083 --> 00:57.449
You're under arrest for kidnapping

00:57.484 --> 00:59.184
and child endangerment.

01:04.891 --> 01:07.092
Okay, what part about, "Let
me out before we get here"

01:07.127 --> 01:08.727
did you have a hard time understanding?

01:08.762 --> 01:10.229
What? You don't want to drive
to work with the boss

01:10.264 --> 01:12.263
in his new, totally unearned,

01:12.298 --> 01:14.699
utterly gauche, and
offensive British sports car?

01:14.734 --> 01:16.536
- No, I didn't.
- Hey, come on.

01:16.536 --> 01:17.768
We run the mother ship of this network.

01:17.803 --> 01:19.403
I'm saying you got to own it.

01:19.439 --> 01:20.438
Stake your flag.

01:22.174 --> 01:23.241
Don't do this again.

