04:44.917 --> 04:47.184
I mean, come on. I wanted
Perrier-Jouet or above.

04:47.220 --> 04:48.652
This is... And that's a cut.

04:50.022 --> 04:52.489
Mm.

04:52.524 --> 04:54.023
I didn't think you'd be in here.

04:54.059 --> 04:55.458
I kind of like this bunking together.

04:55.493 --> 04:58.128
If you want me to find
somewhere else to work...

04:58.163 --> 05:00.296
What is that?

05:00.331 --> 05:01.397
Oh, nothing.

05:01.432 --> 05:03.733
What is this? Not nothing.

05:03.769 --> 05:05.468
Holy shit, Rachel.

05:06.704 --> 05:08.238
Where did you find this?

05:08.273 --> 05:10.306
I found that in the camera truck.

05:10.341 --> 05:12.741
In the camera... Jeremy?

05:12.777 --> 05:15.410
That's a fire-able offense right there.

05:15.445 --> 05:18.914
You can't fire him because
he's good, and he's very fast.

05:18.949 --> 05:21.416
Did you guys have a thing toge...

05:21.451 --> 05:24.052
I'm not judging you, but
this is cr... I mean...

05:25.856 --> 05:28.722
On a happier note,

05:28.758 --> 05:30.057
you're gonna need a ball gown,

05:30.093 --> 05:31.725
and we're leaving work at 6:00 tonight.

05:31.761 --> 05:34.495
The Impact Awards. That's Quinn's thing.

05:34.530 --> 05:36.397
It's our thing.
Tickets go to the showrunner.

05:37.934 --> 05:39.500
I can't. It feels weird.

05:39.535 --> 05:40.835
More like great and overdue, right?

05:40.870 --> 05:42.270
Do you know who else is gonna be there?

05:42.305 --> 05:43.504
Who?

05:43.539 --> 05:45.105
The rest of television,

05:45.140 --> 05:48.074
everyone we're ever gonna want
to work with in our careers.

05:48.110 --> 05:50.510
It's a great opportunity, Rach.

05:50.545 --> 05:51.611
Let's take it.

05:54.116 --> 05:56.783
Welcome back to "Everlasting."

05:56.819 --> 05:58.384
We're at the midway point of the season,

05:58.420 --> 06:00.086
only seven ladies left.

06:00.122 --> 06:04.790
But we have narrowed it down
to your two fan favorites.

06:04.826 --> 06:06.692
Now, of course, Darius
will share a drink with each

06:06.727 --> 06:10.229
and then choose one with
whom he will spend the night.

06:10.264 --> 06:13.432
We have tallied your
millions of votes, America,

06:13.467 --> 06:15.367
and the winners are...

06:18.405 --> 06:19.938
Yael and Dominique.

06:19.973 --> 06:21.206
Oh!

06:25.511 --> 06:26.945
This is so good!

06:28.414 --> 06:29.747
Thank you.

06:29.782 --> 06:32.050
Oh, wow. Ah!

06:32.085 --> 06:34.052
Where are these people?

06:35.521 --> 06:37.287
What do you want, Rachel?

06:37.323 --> 06:39.656
You're trying to sell Yael and Dominique

06:39.691 --> 06:40.924
as the fan favorites?

06:40.960 --> 06:42.625
Well, yeah, anything's possible

06:42.661 --> 06:45.595
since we don't actually
tally those votes.

06:45.630 --> 06:48.465
I mean, I don't even really know
where that phone number goes.

06:48.500 --> 06:50.267
Okay, but, like, why Dominique?

06:50.302 --> 06:53.135
So Hot Rachel gets the overnight.

06:53.171 --> 06:55.271
I mean, if I gave
Darius an actual choice,

06:55.306 --> 06:57.139
then I wouldn't get what I want.

06:57.175 --> 06:59.008
Okay, well, Darius wants Ruby, FYI.

06:59.043 --> 07:01.777
Of course he does. Madison!

07:01.812 --> 07:04.981
Why are we doing overnights
before the final two?

07:05.016 --> 07:06.682
Uh, because I felt that the show needed

07:06.717 --> 07:08.150
a little more spice...

07:08.186 --> 07:11.452
unless you and Coleman
have a different idea.

07:11.488 --> 07:13.188
Maybe you want to give me some notes?

07:15.558 --> 07:17.025
Where's my stylist?

07:17.060 --> 07:18.459
I don't know.

07:18.495 --> 07:19.961
And where are the Impact tickets?

07:19.997 --> 07:22.430
- I don't have them.
- Well, go get them.

07:22.465 --> 07:23.798
I can't.

07:23.833 --> 07:26.234
- Madison...
- No, actually, she can't.

07:27.569 --> 07:29.169
And why is that?

07:29.205 --> 07:30.337
Because I have them.

07:30.373 --> 07:32.172
See, they're for the showrunner,

07:32.208 --> 07:34.474
and Coleman's the showrunner, so...

07:36.145 --> 07:37.144
Get out.

07:41.583 --> 07:42.917
- Quinn
- Out!

07:48.987 --> 07:51.155
Yeah, that's perfect. That's good.

07:51.190 --> 07:53.224
Hey, Jeremy, you got a second?

07:53.259 --> 07:54.069
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah. What's up?

07:54.069 --> 07:56.492
- Guys, could you give us a minute?
- Yeah, you bet.

07:56.527 --> 07:58.361
Um, so, I got some
feedback from the network

07:58.396 --> 07:59.174
about our look this year,

07:59.198 --> 08:00.564
- and they have some concerns.
- Really?

08:00.565 --> 08:01.260
Well, what did they say?

08:01.260 --> 08:02.244
Well, they used words

08:02.244 --> 08:05.735
like "flat," "undynamic,"
"not evolving."

08:05.771 --> 08:07.737
What does that even mean?

08:07.773 --> 08:10.039
Did they mention specific
episodes or scenes or anything?

08:10.075 --> 08:12.690
No, nothing specific. More
of a global discussion.

08:12.690 --> 08:14.076
Anyway, I'm gonna bring
on a visual consultant

08:14.111 --> 08:15.878
to kind of course-correct
the department.

08:15.913 --> 08:17.913
- A visual consultant.
- Mm-hmm.

08:17.948 --> 08:22.151
That sounds... That sounds
a lot like a new D.P.

08:22.186 --> 08:22.820
Am I getting fired?

08:22.820 --> 08:25.220
Absolutely not.

08:25.256 --> 08:27.256
In the meantime, though,
for a little while at least,

08:27.291 --> 08:29.023
I'm gonna have you
move to the insert unit.

08:29.058 --> 08:30.401
The...

08:30.401 --> 08:32.726
I started on the insert unit.

08:34.097 --> 08:36.397
Rachel put you up to this?

08:36.432 --> 08:39.500
My relationship with Rachel
is none of your business.

08:39.534 --> 08:41.735
Well, maybe I should quit.

08:41.770 --> 08:44.038
Yeah, well, you always
have that option, don't you?

08:47.876 --> 08:49.776
Hey.

08:49.812 --> 08:51.938
- You look great.
- Hi.

08:51.938 --> 08:54.028
Um, are you sure about this dress?

08:54.028 --> 08:55.048
It's not too revealing?

08:55.048 --> 08:55.948
I don't think so.

08:55.948 --> 08:57.449
I mean, this is the first overnight.

08:57.449 --> 09:01.271
It's a really big deal, and...
your competition...

09:02.156 --> 09:03.956
Uh, yeah, that's kind of
what I'm talking about.

09:03.991 --> 09:05.590
I don't want Darius to think
I'm trying too hard.

09:05.626 --> 09:07.526
Okay, well, you better try something.

09:07.561 --> 09:09.094
What are you talking about?

09:09.130 --> 09:10.462
They voted for me.

09:10.497 --> 09:12.064
Right.

09:12.099 --> 09:13.532
Yeah, well, tonight's about Darius,

09:13.567 --> 09:15.567
and, honestly, the
guy hasn't noticed you.

09:15.602 --> 09:17.303
What? I'm a basketball player.

09:17.338 --> 09:18.737
I'm a foot taller than everyone.

09:18.772 --> 09:21.072
For better or for worse,
Yael made herself known,

09:21.107 --> 09:23.041
so if you really want to stick around...

09:23.076 --> 09:25.409
What should I do?

09:31.617 --> 09:33.784
America has done the difficult work

09:33.820 --> 09:37.221
and narrowed the field
down to Yael and Dominique.

09:37.256 --> 09:39.923
So, what do you say, Darius?

09:39.959 --> 09:41.424
Thank you, America.

09:41.460 --> 09:42.726
Now, obviously,

09:42.761 --> 09:44.594
the final decision is yours, of course,

09:44.629 --> 09:47.797
but to help you, we have
asked Yael and Dominique

09:47.833 --> 09:50.667
to come up with their
very own specialty drink

09:50.702 --> 09:52.302
to give you a little
insight on what an evening

09:52.338 --> 09:54.070
with each one of these
beauties might have in store.

09:54.105 --> 09:55.804
It should be Ruby, and you know it,

09:55.840 --> 09:57.173
after last's week's, like,

09:57.208 --> 09:59.308
beautiful, Nubian
lovefest that I captured.

09:59.344 --> 09:59.961
- Jay...
- No.

09:59.985 --> 10:01.979
You brought her
here for the wrong reasons.

10:01.980 --> 10:04.254
Rach, you thought she'd be gone
in two episodes, but guess what?

10:04.515 --> 10:07.150
What's happening between them is real,

10:07.185 --> 10:09.818
and that in itself is a
beautiful story worth telling.

10:09.853 --> 10:11.753
Okay. So maybe it'll be her.

10:11.789 --> 10:13.121
- How?
- Will you stop?

10:13.157 --> 10:15.057
Seriously, shut up.

10:15.092 --> 10:16.758
Have some faith.

10:16.794 --> 10:20.162
A splash of lime juice, just
a kiss of orange blossom,

10:20.197 --> 10:21.897
three ounces of Cuervo.

10:21.932 --> 10:23.665
There it is...

10:23.701 --> 10:25.266
with raspberries and mint.

10:25.302 --> 10:27.902
I mean, she really is
sex on a stick, isn't she?

10:27.937 --> 10:29.503
- Not bad.

10:29.538 --> 10:31.772
I call it an Uncharted Depth...

10:31.808 --> 10:33.240
Uncharted Depth.

10:33.275 --> 10:35.409
A drink which reveals itself over time.

10:35.444 --> 10:36.510
I'm that way, too.

10:36.545 --> 10:38.079
People often get

10:38.114 --> 10:39.580
the wrong impression
'cause of the way I look,

10:39.615 --> 10:40.981
but I never spend the night with someone

10:41.017 --> 10:42.316
unless I'm truly serious about them.

10:42.351 --> 10:44.283
"America, welcome to my boobs."

10:44.319 --> 10:45.383
- Dominique.
- I don't have

10:45.407 --> 10:47.221
a fancy cocktail for you

10:47.222 --> 10:49.455
because I'm all about
honesty, integrity,

10:49.490 --> 10:51.091
and knowing what you're gonna get.

10:51.126 --> 10:54.127
Ugh! In other words,
a snoozefest in bed.

10:54.162 --> 10:55.695
She looks like a magician.

10:55.731 --> 10:58.965
Simple glass of red wine...
and the truth.

11:00.668 --> 11:02.935
If you're gonna be spending
the night with one of us,

11:02.970 --> 11:04.336
it should probably be the one

11:04.371 --> 11:05.971
who's not sleeping with the crew.

11:06.006 --> 11:08.807
What? What? Wait.

11:08.843 --> 11:10.342
What did she just say? Um...

11:10.377 --> 11:11.710
Excuse me?

11:11.746 --> 11:12.945
- Are you saying she...
- Darius.

11:12.980 --> 11:14.279
You deserve someone who's here

11:14.314 --> 11:15.547
just for you, Darius.

11:15.582 --> 11:16.782
I am here for him.

11:16.817 --> 11:18.315
You got a funny way of showing it.

11:18.351 --> 11:19.784
- Don't listen to this.
- She lied to your face.

11:19.819 --> 11:21.185
- Are you kidding me?
- She's been lying to you.

11:21.221 --> 11:22.787
- Quit this.
- How do you get the nerve...

11:26.926 --> 11:29.360
Jeremy, what are you doing?

11:29.395 --> 11:30.628
What, are you drunk?

11:30.663 --> 11:32.130
